title: SFH on medical incident reports
content_text:
p>
Following is the transcript of remarks (English portion) made by the 
Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, at a stand-up media session 
after attending the Technical Consultation on Health Sector Response to 
HIV/AIDS among Men who have sex with Men today (February 18): Reporter: (Caritas Medical Centre report) Secretary for Food and Health: I think the report from the Caritas Medical 
Centre reflects that there are deficiencies in the decision and the 
judgement of the two administrators. And taking into consideration that both

judgement of the two administrators. And taking into consideration that both 
of them have been in their position for a relatively short time, I think the 
penalty is sufficient. More importantly, we should take lessons from what 
happened to ensure that the hospital develops a patient-centred policy, and 
particularly the accident and emergency department, in order to formulate 
better supporting services for the department and the hospital. I think the 
main message for this report is able to learn from mistakes and also to

main message for this report is able to learn from mistakes and also to 
correct them as soon as possible. Reporter: (What else can you do on Pamela Youde Nethersole Eastern Hospital 
report) Secretary for Food and Health: Of course, I am disappointed with the lack of 
findings in the report regarding the reasons for losing the baby body and 
the difficulties in locating the whereabouts of the body. This will give 
grave concerns to the parents and also the family members. I have already 
said that anybody who made mistakes can be excusable but anybody who lied

said that anybody who made mistakes can be excusable but anybody who lied 
about making mistakes is inexcusable. I think it is important that we take 
very seriously the staff concerned who have provided wrong information to 
the hospital, to the family members of this baby as well as to the police.
 Reporter: Do you think the hospital chief should step down? Secretary for Food and Health: No, I think she has tried her best to solve

and investigate this problem. Reporter: (Delay of the bird flu report in Yuen Long farm) Secretary for Food and Health: The report is being processed mainly because we have to recommend some new biosecurity measures to the farmers. And the Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department is going through the process of educating the farmers right now. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript.)
